2022 was dope. Definitely an interesting one to sum up. I feel this way every year but maybe it’s bc I’m always wanting more - but it seemed like another building year to set myself up for the next. It certainly was one of the most fun, scary and accomplishing years yet. As with any year this one came with lots of hurdles and lots of highs. 

I was able to grow my businesses, dive into a few new ones, grind through 365 days while continuing to setup up my future, build cars I would have never imagined owning, created amazing memories and most importantly I turned more friends into family. 

Big thank you to @blondebiography for being the most supportive women ever. If you didn’t know, she’s my rock, my shelter, my best friend and she always knows how to keep my crazy mind on track 🙃

Sometimes I feel some type of way writing these posts but it always feels good to reflect & connect with people I don’t get to see too often. For that, it’s worth it. 

To all the amazing friends, family, strangers, creators and builders out there - I see you and I am grateful & honored that so many of you choose to network with me & follow my journey. 143 🖤

See all you goons in 2023. A another chance for us to get it right and another year where we once again, level up more than once! LFG. 📈

In the midst of working entirely way too much over the last two weeks, I managed to pull off some changes on the rx7 before riverside. 

The rx7 was always the no fucs given build. To not think but do. My “no rules” build. I removed almost all the stickers for a more mature look that I feel like I’ve grown into. Josh Newton and I paint matched my fairly rare (and once new in box from the 90’s) ganador mirrors. My boy filled some body work & key holes during the process to give it an even more smooth appearance than the car already had. 

Additionally, I added the final piece to my Next Nippon Japan Miracle X bar. All of which was sourced and imported over the years as gifts from the homie @jakefromvaded, so thanks Jake! 

I’ll be grinding into the night to add a few engine bits, change the wheels up and some other details that shall remained unmentioned - for the simple fact that something very special happens when someone notices a discreet unmentioned move you make on a build with this much going on. Said encounter often creates a connection that can last forever, maybe even a new friend or two. 

If anyone on here is sliding to @riversidechattanooga come check out the rotary, the new Vaded gear that we’ve been working on for the better part of winter & lastly, come vibe with the amazing enthusiasts and spectators that this event brings together. It certainly isn’t one to miss! 

Safe travels & I’ll see you tomorrow Chattanooga! Damn! I’m super excited. LFG! 🖤

Vaded Mob would like to welcome you to our 7th annual Gatlinburg Premeet!

With this being SE’s biggest premeet on their tour, we have gained permitted access to 1,200 parking spaces to accommodate this event once again. The gates will open at 4pm on Friday 9/29 and the event will end at 9pm. 

Entry fee is $15 a car & $5 per spectator. No vehicles will be granted access with a spectator ticket therefore, spectators will be asked to ride with a vehicle ticket holder, uber or get dropped off. 

Spectators tickets can be purchased at the entry gates but we encourage that premeet vehicles pre-register to guarantee a spot as the event will likely sell out. 

This will ensure the event runs more smoothly than years past and the registration will double for less traffic. We greatly appreciate your understanding in this regard. 

To be compliant with ordinances; the police, have asked us to put a cap on the vehicle entries to 1200 cars - pre sold tickets only (via foat website (in bio) - on or after Friday 9/8). This link will be active at 10am EST to give everyone a fair chance at getting a spot. Vendors will be able to also register with this link. 

The event will have food on site, a beer garden, automotive lifestyle vendors and two entrances and exits for your convenience. We will post & pin a road map for both entrances.

Sevierville police will be on site to help keep traffic flowing and also keep the venue and all attendees safe to ensure a return for next year.

Special thanks to our sponsors, vendors & attendees! See you in the mountains!

Lately, I feel like I’ve been having a hard time to find things to be excited for. Well, all that changed over the last few weeks when my team and I managed to pull together something that I had quite of bit of doubt on. 

After continuously getting turned down and denied in 3 different cities and 6 different venues, I saw a small glimpse of chance to make this pre-meet happen once again at our old stomping grounds. 

With this event having got as big as it has, it’s been very tough to keep things under control for everyone involved. With that being said, we made a big push to continue to work with the city of Sevierville and their local PD officers to bring back the PreMeet to the beautiful Smokies Stadium once again. 

We came to an agreement to do a presale based event to keep traffic and other orders under control. All of which to my surprise, SOLD OUT in a days time! Spectator entry will still be available at the gates, tho the lot is officially full in regards to parking.

Deep down, I feel like excitement holds the key to my ambition. So thank you for creating that and believing in us at @vadedmob

Thank you to @charlan.se & the whole entire @slammedenuff staff for trusting us with this for the 7th year in a fkn row! I still can’t believe we beat y’all in flippy cup game 8 years ago to lock this in. It’s crazy to look back on and see what it’s come to today. 

This event has taken a team of people with 100’s of hours of work. From myself and my team - we thank you. Your support speaks volumes and we can’t wait to warm up your Gatlinburg weekend Friday, September 29th with over 20 vendors and 1200 cars 🖤

I can’t believe it’s already Gatlinburg week! Last few weeks have been pure chaos to say the least. 

Nonetheless, I’m super stoked to share what I call, my old school vs new school look on the FD. I originally imported these T7R2p’s for the chaser but figured I’d rock them thru the mountains. Of course I had to wrap them in @toyotires 

Additionally, @fishfabllc and I relocated the radiator spout to fit up these custom made carbon fiber inserts which now cover my fender liners. Something that has been bugging me for years with this engine bay. This allowed me to remove half of the finder liners & lower the car down a bit more. 

Even more exciting tho, is this new @vadedmob booth & box wall. The old 10x10 lasted us a good 7 years but we simply outgrew it in a beautiful way. I did my best to keep the designs on the tent original & OG while still throwing a taste of that new new to keep things fresh. 

All this aside, I’m most stoked to share the new Vaded Gatlinburg release with my people, in one of my favorite states, with one of the most amazing cultures I’ve been blessed enough to be involved with. I never expect sales, but all I ask is you stop by, say hi and check out what we’ve been up to! I hope you like what my team and I have created for this massive week and I hope you all travel safe into the Smokies! 

Looking forward 🖤⛰️

Gatlinburg 2023…let me start by saying this was the most fun Gatlinburg yet. 

It really took a lot personally to get here and to be completely honest w you, I feel like 65 hour work weeks are the new 40. I’ve pushed myself harder than I ever have this year. I’ve gained even more ambition and even more soul. 

I can’t even lie. I cried tears of joy on the way home. I do my best to reflect on my drive to and from the smokies. A chance to breathe and a chance to soak in what’s about to happen and what has happened in this event and most importantly, life as a whole. 

I’m sure you know at this point, I feel very strongly about this specific event. It’s where Vaded was unveiled at in 2016 and often it’s where we gather & grow at.

Thursday I was able to join Shaleek Tukes on the @streetalphapodcast, which I am SO excited to have been able to share my story with. Everything from where I started as a kid to what I’ve grown into today. 

As for Friday and our event, it was perfect. I can’t wait to reveal what my media team and I have created for the YouTube channel! 

The SE show was a blast. Vaded crushed it as a small business and I’m forever grateful. Vending gives me a chance to share my creative outlet with others, make new friends & share intimate stories with one another. 

Attendance Saturday was DEEP. Sunday it tapered off a bit and the judging was certainly…well, let’s say interesting.

In conclusion, I couldn’t be more proud of my team, from production to my street club. We crushed it. 

I know we’re senior mob but this year, we had a whole new booth set up, an attendance of 20 vehicles into the show, 6 new wheel set ups on display, 4 new trunk set up’s, 3 color changes, 3 candy painted cars, hella eye to detail changes and two entirely new builds. On top of all this, I watched my team meet with strangers, answer questions & help make the culture excel in amazing way. 

The energy and vibes of these guys & girls are simply unmatched. I’ve met 1,000’s of people throughout life but this team simply doesn’t miss. Quite literally some of the most incredible human beings I’ve ever met. To me, that’s the biggest W you can ask for.

I’m excited to share with you all something that I’ve been working on for the better part of a year. 

The unveil of my Midnight Purple 3, 2JZ swapped, shaved & tucked JZX100 Toyota Chaser - in Las Vegas at the SEMA show on the notorious ToyoTread Pass. 

This has been a dream of mine since first visiting SEMA back in 2017. Hailing a car I imported from Japan and bringing it to a SEMA Treadpass level with the best team ever. The build is a combination of all the knowledge and styling I’ve absorbed over the years - and put into one. 

I want to start by saying I built this car in some of the most pressing times of my life. I work so hard and move so fast in so many different directions that it’s hard to even fathom that we’ve pulled this off. 

I certainly couldn’t have done it w out my people. I’ll start with @fishfabllc - Words can’t express how amazingly you executed the tubbing & filling process on the engine bay - thank you for everything. 

To my @eccentric_motorsports boys, thank you for the strong and positive energy, for letting me come work on the car so often, for letting me drop the motor in for the first time and for assembling me such a beautifully executed 2JZ motor!

Biggest up to JP for the beautiful flow coated quadruple cleared paint job, the amazing ghost lace styled roof and the difficult but magnificent hood piece!

To my ace @endless_visuals, thank you for always pushing thru with editing for the channel and photo work!

I want to express my sincere appreciation to @toyotires. Your ongoing support has helped me excel immensely over the years. To @haltechecu, @serialnine suspension components, @workwheelsjapan, @chasebays and @vibrant_performance - thank you all for making such incredible products and for your support on the project. 

Lastly, thank you from the bottom of my heart to my Vaded homies and all of my friends / family. I couldn’t do this without you all!

I finally feel like I’ve done it all. The support over the years of my building “career”, all the likes, shares, calls & texts have never gone unnoticed! Time for me to go steal some energy from Las Vegas, baby! 

Here’s to keeping the art alive! 🖤
Super stoked to unveil this at SEMA! If you catch us on the treadpass be sure to say what’s up!

Life comes at you way too fast. Over the last year, I faced some difficult moments and I even reached my breaking point three different times. I learned that I’ve had to risk the fall to know how it feels to fly and that a stronger, better me will be born during times that challenge me the most.

Nonetheless, I’m blessed to be embracing another year of growth, wisdom & purpose found. Thank you for the immense amount of love this week. I just realized if you have friends in Japan, your birthday is actually two days long 😉

Here’s to expanding the network to more time zones, more life, more goals, accomplishments & endlessly gaining knowledge. I’m grateful to have the most amazing friends and an incredible family. I’m excited to close out the year strong and continuing to be 100% unfuckwitable in 2024. 

The years teach much which the days never knew. The great thing about getting older is that you don’t lose all the other ages you’ve gained. 

Yesterday, I added another candle of knowledge and wisdom to life, with hopes that it gives me power to enlighten the whole world.

In the end, it’s not the years in your life that count. It’s the life in your years. LFG! 🖤
I couldn’t have asked for a better group of guys to spend 5 days in the mountains shredding and partying! We had entirely too much fun. Until next year Colorado! 🤙🏼🏂🎿
